  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together olive oil, onion, garlic, ginger, cumin, paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the sea bass fillets to the bowl and coat with the marinade.",
    "Let the fillets marinate for 15 minutes.",
    "In a large tagine or Dutch oven, combine the marinated fillets and preserved lemons.",
    "Cover the tagine and bake for 20 minutes.",
    "Remove the tagine from the oven and let it cool for 5 minutes.",
    "Serve the sea bass hot, garnished with fresh parsley and crusty bread on the side."
